        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 2:27PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 227 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southeast of Bronco, or 7 miles west of Plains. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Plains and Bronco.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
